cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on reinforcement learning for robotics and includes experiments on a surgical robot. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a new model-based reinforcement learning algorithm. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with learning complex maneuvers and handling constraints. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses iterative improvement guarantees for the proposed algorithm. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is less likely but still possible as some of the benchmarks involve navigation and manipulation tasks that may require visual perception.
